Referred to Committee on Growth and Infrastructure
SUMMARY—Revises provisions governing the towing of motor
vehicles. (BDR 43-821)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: No.
Effect on the State: Yes.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to motor vehicles; revising provisions governing
the disposition of certain vehicles abandoned on public or
private property; revising the value of a vehicle for which
a junk certificate may be issued by the Department of
Motor Vehicles; prohibiting the operator of a tow car
from falsely reporting the location of the operator or tow
car to a law enforcement agency for certain purposes; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law: (1) authorizes certain persons and law enforcement agencies to
2 request the removal of a vehicle that has been abandoned on public or private
3 property; and (2) requires the person who requests such a removal to inquire into
4 whether the vehicle was stolen and the identity of the vehicle’s owner. (NRS
5 487.230, 487.235) Existing law requires a person who removed an abandoned
6 vehicle to notify the registered owner and any person having a security interest in
7 the vehicle by registered or certified mail that the vehicle has been removed and
8 will be junked, dismantled or otherwise disposed of unless the owner or the person
9 having the security interest responds and pays the costs of removal. (NRS 487.250)
10 Existing law additionally requires a tow operator to notify the registered and legal
11 owner of a vehicle if the vehicle was towed and placed in storage at the request of
12 someone other than the owner or the owner’s authorized agent. (NRS 706.4479)
13 Existing law authorizes the Department of Motor Vehicles to issue a junk
14 certificate to a tow operator or automobile wrecker for a vehicle that: (1) has been
15 discarded or abandoned; (2) has been ruined, wrecked, dismantled or rendered
16 inoperative; (3) is unfit for further use in accordance with the vehicle’s original
-
