17 purpose; (4) is unregistered or is not reclaimed by the registered owner or person
18 having a security interest in the vehicle within a certain period of time; and (5) has
19 value principally as scrap which does not exceed $200. (NRS 487.260) Section 4 of
20 this bill increases the value of a vehicle for which a junk certificate may be issued
21 to include a vehicle which has value principally as scrap which does not exceed
22 $500. Sections 1 and 2 of this bill authorize certain persons, with respect to an
23 abandoned, unregistered vehicle which appears likely to be appraised as a junk
24 vehicle and for which the identity of the owner is not known or readily
25 ascertainable, to affix to the vehicle a notice that if the abandoned vehicle is not
26 removed from the public or private property within 5 days, the vehicle is subject to
27 being junked, dismantled or otherwise disposed of. If this notice is affixed to an
28 unregistered vehicle which is appraised as a junk vehicle, sections 1-5 of this bill
29 excuse the person or law enforcement agency that authorized the removal of the
30 vehicle and the tow operator who removed the vehicle from other provisions
31 requiring such persons to make inquiries into the identity of the owner of the
32 vehicle and provide the owner with certain notice regarding the removal of the
33 vehicle. Section 4 requires the person or law enforcement agency that authorized
34 the removal of the vehicle to provide the contact information of the automobile
35 wrecker or tow operator who removed the vehicle if contacted by the vehicle’s
36 owner. Section 4 authorizes an automobile wrecker or tow operator who receives a
37 junk certificate for an abandoned vehicle to which such a notice has been affixed to
38 dispose of the vehicle not earlier than 48 hours after the vehicle arrives and is
39 registered at the place of storage.
40 Existing law prohibits a law enforcement agency that maintains and uses a list
41 of tow cars which are called by that agency to provide towing from including an
42 operator of a tow car on that list unless the operator meets certain requirements.
43 (NRS 706.4485) Section 6 of this bill prohibits an operator of a tow car from using
44 any software, device or other means to falsely report the location of the operator or
45 tow car to a law enforcement agency for the purpose of securing a request from the
46 law enforcement agency to provide towing services.
